1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,960
මෙය ... විය නොහැක.

2
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,870
සිදුවන්නේ කුමක් ද?!

3
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,330
එතකොට හරියටම,

4
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:08,160
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
ජෙනින් බවට පත් වූ තරුණ ෂිනෝබි ,

5
00:01:08,870 --> 00:01:13,160
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
ජොනින් නැති වූ ගමක් කරා ගමන් කළහ.

6
00:01:14,830 --> 00:01:19,620
ඒ අතර 
අනාවැකියේ දරුවා ... නරුටෝ ද විය.

7
00:02:56,450 --> 00:03:00,700
ජිරයියා නින්ජා ලියවිලි: 
නරුටෝ හි වීරයා 
පිළිබඳ සෙවීමේ මෙහෙයුමේ කතාව

8
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:23,070
සිදුවුයේ කුමක් ද?

9
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:27,410
ඔබ දන්නා යමක් 
ඇත්නම් කරුණාකර මට කියන්න ... ඒ කුමක් වුවත්.

10
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,360
මට කණගාටුයි.

11
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:32,740
ඉසුමෝ සහ කොටෙට්සු 
හදිසියේම අතුරුදහන් වූහ

12
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,990
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
මම පුළුවන් තරම් වේගයෙන් එතැනින් පිටව ගියෙමි ...

13
00:03:35,570 --> 00:03:39,780
ඇත්තම කිව්වොත්, මම 
මෙතැනට ගියේ කෙසේදැයි මට මතක නැත .

14
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:42,740
මට තේරෙනවා.

15
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:44,950
ඒ සියල්ල ඔබට ඉදිරිපත් කිරීම ගැන මට කණගාටුයි 
.

16
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:50,700
නමුත් ඔබට 
සුළු දෙයක් මතක තිබුනත් කරුණාකර මට කියන්න.

17
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:02,110
අගේ…

18
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:03,820
අගේහා සමනලයෙක් ...

19
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,950
ඔහු කතා කරන්නේ 
ෂිනෝබි අගේහා ගැන විය හැකිය ...

20
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,360
මෙම සමය තුළ,

21
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:17,570
it's not unusual to see them
in the forest near that village.

22
00:04:17,570 --> 00:04:19,860
Is it a poisonous butterfly?

23
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:21,610
No.

24
00:04:21,740 --> 00:04:25,240
Its powdery scales
stimulate chakra flow

25
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:28,700
and it's even a main ingredient
in food pills.

26
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:34,660
I can't believe Izumo and Kotetsu
were beaten so easily…

27
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:44,490
Looks like we're all set.

28
00:04:47,530 --> 00:04:49,360
No, Team 7 is still…

29
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:53,320
Sorry, Team 7 is late.

30
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:56,160
We're all here now.

31
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:59,610
I know it's sudden,
but let me go over the mission.

32
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:04,860
I hope its way more exciting
than looking for a lost cat.

33
00:05:07,530 --> 00:05:09,740
This mission is very important.

34
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:15,410
Three teams of shinobi that were
dispatched on secret missions

35
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:18,110
have all gone missing.

36
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:21,860
Your mission is to
search and find them.

37
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:26,700
Yahoo!

38
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:31,280
However, you are to contact
the Hidden Leaf

39
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:33,530
the moment they are found.

40
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:36,110
Any attempts at rescue
are forbidden.

41
00:05:37,990 --> 00:05:39,200
Why?!

42
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,530
Considering who's been chosen,

43
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:47,660
the answer should be
pretty obvious to everyone.

44
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:52,700
Is it because we're all elite ninja
overflowing with talent?!

45
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:59,070
Nearly all the shinobi who
went missing are capable jonin…

46
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:02,610
But the only one who was able to
make it back to the village,

47
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:03,660
was a genin.

48
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:09,660
So it could mean, experience
and maturity are being targeted.

49
00:06:10,530 --> 00:06:11,660
Which means?

50
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:15,570
In other words, we were picked
because we're newbies

51
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:17,570
who just became genin.

52
00:06:17,950 --> 00:06:20,070
Well, you could put it that way…

53
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,360
What?

54
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:23,450
Is that all?

55
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:29,660
Naruto, you will most likely
be the one who—

56
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,200
Everyone, stop!

57
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,160
What is it?

58
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:46,660
Isn't our target village
further ahead?

59
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:47,820
Look.

60
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,240
What's that?

61
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:53,410
Shinobi Ageha?

62
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,780
All right! I'm gonna go catch 'em!

63
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,160
Hey! You!

64
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:00,110
That's really not necessary…

65
00:07:00,570 --> 00:07:01,530
I'll bring him back!

66
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:02,990
Oh really?

67
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,360
Come on!

68
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:05,700
Oh boy…

69
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,530
Eight Trigrams Grid Palm!

70
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,700
This is…

71
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:53,860
Kakashi Sensei!

72
00:07:59,990 --> 00:08:01,820
Naruto! Get back here right now!

73
00:08:03,910 --> 00:08:05,490
What the hell?

74
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:07,320
I almost had it!

75
00:08:07,490 --> 00:08:09,700
Don't go off on your own
during a mission.

76
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,410
What did you just say?

77
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:14,530
I don't take orders from you!

78
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:17,030
What? This isn't an order!

79
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,530
I'm telling you to act
more like a shinobi!

80
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:21,240
Going off on your own
puts others in—

81
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:23,990
Sasuke!
Kakashi Sensei's in trouble!

82
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,610
– What happened?
– Kakashi Sensei's…

83
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:31,410
When I noticed, he…

84
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:34,700
He was dragged underground, huh?

85
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,030
No way!

86
00:08:40,530 --> 00:08:41,570
What—!

87
00:08:51,530 --> 00:08:52,530
Asuma!

88
00:08:55,530 --> 00:08:57,240
Damn it…
They got him.

89
00:08:57,740 --> 00:09:00,320
What? What happened?

90
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:02,320
Where's Asuma Sensei?

91
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:04,530
I-I don't know…

92
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:09,700
Is this…

93
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:13,070
…sensation, chakra?!

94
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,490
What happened, Akamaru?!

95
00:09:20,570 --> 00:09:23,610
Akamaru's barking not because of
something happening.

96
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,360
It's because
he lost track of Kurenai Sensei

97
00:09:26,450 --> 00:09:28,490
who should be present.

98
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:40,740
What is this?

99
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:42,700
Byakugan!

100
00:09:46,990 --> 00:09:49,280
There's a current of chakra
underground…

101
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,570
Where is it coming from?

102
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:57,410
Neji! Where are you going?

103
00:09:57,490 --> 00:09:58,660
I want to check something!

104
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:00,160
Stay with Guy!

105
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:06,610
Guy Sensei!

106
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:08,160
Does your chest hurt?!

107
00:10:08,570 --> 00:10:11,240
It's nothing that
a little perseverance can't…

108
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,990
Guy Sensei!

109
00:10:15,070 --> 00:10:16,570
Don't push yourself!

110
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:20,030
I'll go get some water.

111
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:23,360
Tenten, stay and watch Guy Sensei.

112
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:24,530
All right!

113
00:10:45,990 --> 00:10:46,990
What happened?

114
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,780
Guy Sensei felt sick and…

115
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,320
Where's Guy Sensei?!

116
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:56,110
Black vine-like things sprang up,

117
00:10:56,860 --> 00:11:00,280
wrapped around Sensei,
and pulled him underground.

118
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,490
What?

119
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,490
The current of chakra is gone.

120
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,070
Hey!

121
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:24,320
Kakashi Sensei is probably
in enemy hands.

122
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,820
What are we supposed to do?

123
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,530
What else is there to do?!

124
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:31,030
We're gonna find him no matter what
and get him back!

125
00:11:31,530 --> 00:11:32,660
Damn it.

126
00:11:32,820 --> 00:11:35,320
I'm never giving up!

127
00:11:46,970 --> 00:11:48,970
Hey, what are we going to do?

128
00:11:49,470 --> 00:11:51,340
What's going to happen?

129
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,510
First, we should contact
the other teams,

130
00:11:54,880 --> 00:12:00,590
then contact the Leaf Village
like Lord Hokage ordered, right?

131
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:03,800
Wait.

132
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:05,340
Don't move!

133
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,840
What?

134
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:10,880
Damn it.

135
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:15,260
What the Fourth Hokage feared
would happen just happened…

136
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:16,380
Huh?!

137
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,260
It's probably safe to assume that

138
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:22,720
the same thing has happened
to the other team captains.

139
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:24,680
The other teams?

140
00:12:24,930 --> 00:12:26,590
So it's not only us…

141
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,800
But Sasuke and Kiba and…

142
00:12:28,970 --> 00:12:31,720
Everyone's been left behind?

143
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,090
Yeah…

144
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:37,090
I just hope Kakashi's team isn't
arguing with each other right now…

145
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:40,010
Since they have someone
who can be a real drag.

146
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,510
Why you—!

147
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:44,300
Wait, you loser!

148
00:12:44,970 --> 00:12:45,880
I already told you!

149
00:12:45,970 --> 00:12:47,680
I'm not giving up!

150
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:49,840
But where are you going?

151
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,800
Well, I don't know, but…

152
00:12:53,050 --> 00:12:56,550
Are you really the son of
the Fourth Hokage?

153
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:02,300
What did you say?!

154
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:04,050
Do you really think the Hokage
would send us out

155
00:13:04,130 --> 00:13:06,880
without making any
preventive measures beforehand?

156
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:11,050
I saw the Hokage
pass out special kunai

157
00:13:11,130 --> 00:13:12,970
to the captains, back then.

158
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,590
Special kunai?

159
00:13:15,970 --> 00:13:16,970
Yeah…

160
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,800
The one he marks when he uses

161
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,800
the Transportation Ninjutsu
to teleport.

162
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:27,010
As long as the mark is there,
he can track anyone, anywhere.

163
00:13:31,260 --> 00:13:33,050
Transportation Ninjutsu?

164
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:36,630
You know what
the Summoning Jutsu is, right?

165
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,930
Uh…yeah!

166
00:13:39,010 --> 00:13:40,840
Think of it as
a type of that jutsu.

167
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:43,840
The special kunai is the target

168
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,800
and no matter
how far away you are…

169
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:49,130
you can transport to the kunai
in an instant…

170
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,800
Lord Fourth is the only one
who can use that jutsu right now.

171
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:54,840
I see. I gotta admit…

172
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,510
My Dad's pretty awesome!

173
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:57,680
Wait!

174
00:13:57,970 --> 00:14:00,510
I don't think…
that's going to happen.

175
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:06,380
Huh? That's…

176
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,720
I found it at the spot right now.

177
00:14:10,010 --> 00:14:12,010
This is the worst situation
we can be in…

178
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:22,880
I think I can visualize Lee making
a big fuss over Guy Sensei.

179
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:28,380
Guy Sensei! Guy Sensei!
Guy Sensei! Guy Sensei!

180
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:29,800
Wait, Lee!

181
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:31,050
Calm down!

182
00:14:31,130 --> 00:14:33,760
That's impossible for me!

183
00:14:33,970 --> 00:14:38,340
Is the Shinobi Code more important
to you two than Guy Sensei's life?!

184
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,090
Don't get the wrong idea!

185
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:43,880
You blockhead!

186
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:49,510
Guy…Sensei.

187
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,840
What are you doing?

188
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,010
Just listen!

189
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:00,970
Just before Guy went missing,

190
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:03,510
there was an unusual current
of chakra underground.

191
00:15:04,930 --> 00:15:06,720
You saw it with your Byakugan?

192
00:15:07,130 --> 00:15:10,180
Yeah. But it's disappeared now.

193
00:15:10,970 --> 00:15:13,970
So, I'd like to check in on
the status of the other teams.

194
00:15:14,970 --> 00:15:17,800
Linking up with the other teams
is our priority right now.

195
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:26,550
So, the key players
will be Kurenai's team.

196
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,930
How so?

197
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,880
Kiba's sense of smell,

198
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,720
Hinata's Byakugan and
Shino's Parasitic Insects…

199
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,840
With their sensory skills,

200
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:37,930
it will be easy to find the current
locations of the other three teams.

201
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,630
And they can probably find

202
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:44,800
the location where
the team captains are being held.

203
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:45,930
You're right!

204
00:15:46,430 --> 00:15:49,130
That would make it way faster than
just proceeding blindly.

205
00:15:49,380 --> 00:15:50,590
In situations like this,

206
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:53,880
panic and proceeding without
thinking is our worst enemy.

207
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,260
It makes more work for everybody.

208
00:15:56,930 --> 00:16:00,010
So until we join up
with Kurenai's team…

209
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:01,970
…we'll just sit tight.

210
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:10,010
Choji must've had
barbeque last night…

211
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:12,220
– Kiba!
– Kiba!

212
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,090
– How is it going?
– Hey!

213
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:17,010
Asuma's team is over that way.

214
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:21,800
Those guys aren't moving at all.

215
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,880
They know we're looking for them.

216
00:16:24,630 --> 00:16:26,840
They're just sitting back
and resting.

217
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:30,510
In any case, let's join up
with Shikamaru quickly.

218
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:34,680
Then we'll pass on his ideas
to the other teams,

219
00:16:35,010 --> 00:16:36,380
and come up with a unified plan.

220
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:37,970
That's because I have a feeling

221
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:41,590
there's someone who's going to
act without thinking through things…

222
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:45,630
And that's where
our abilities come in.

223
00:16:46,090 --> 00:16:47,800
Exactly!

224
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,510
Shikamaru's acclaimed intellect
still needs us!

225
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,840
According to the plan,
Kurenai's team should be over here.

226
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:03,220
Right.

227
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:25,930
Blood?!

228
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:43,090
I have already cursed you.

229
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:44,510
Huh?

230
00:17:45,590 --> 00:17:47,590
Preparations for the ritual
are complete!

231
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:53,510
Now!

232
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:58,550
Let's experience
the ultimate pain together!

233
00:17:58,630 --> 00:17:59,970
What's with this guy?

234
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:01,800
He keeps talking about
curses and rituals?

235
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:03,930
He's dangerous!

236
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,010
– Naruto!
– Naruto?!

237
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:28,590
Doesn't it hurt?

238
00:18:28,930 --> 00:18:32,050
It's gonna be excruciating
so prepare yourself…

239
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:38,510
It's god's commandment!
Tremble in fear!

240
00:18:48,930 --> 00:18:50,800
He's fast asleep.

241
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:54,050
He may seem so,
but he wakes up sharp and alert.

242
00:18:54,380 --> 00:18:57,090
Besides,
it helps replenish his energy.

243
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,340
You're too easy on Choji.

244
00:19:00,260 --> 00:19:01,590
And you're too tough.

245
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:16,970
I knew something was up.

246
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,630
I totally thought it would
happen later though.

247
00:19:20,090 --> 00:19:22,840
I should have known they weren't
going to let us rest so easily.

248
00:19:26,050 --> 00:19:27,180
It's coming!

249
00:19:29,510 --> 00:19:30,720
Paper Shuriken!

250
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:38,090
Wind Style: Gale Palm!

251
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:46,840
Damn it… We have to
get out of this Paper Storm…

252
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:50,380
Choji! Can you break it apart?!

253
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,590
I've had enough rest!

254
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,840
Expansion Jutsu!

255
00:19:56,380 --> 00:19:58,510
Human Boulder!

256
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:01,340
Roll, roll, roll, roll!

257
00:20:01,430 --> 00:20:03,840
Roll, roll, roll, roll!

258
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:06,720
– Roll, roll, roll, roll!
– Water Style: Raging Waves!

259
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,010
You're the ones!

260
00:20:27,970 --> 00:20:31,220
You guys took Asuma Sensei, right?

261
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:33,260
Bring Asuma Sensei back!

262
00:20:40,050 --> 00:20:41,260
Just who the hell…

263
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:42,970
…are you?

264
00:20:49,630 --> 00:20:52,970
Don't think you can
escape my curse!

265
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:55,720
The shinobi world is cursed!

266
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,590
Just give up!

267
00:22:37,610 --> 00:22:40,200
When the man in the strange cloak,

268
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,240
impaled himself
with his pointed scythe

269
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:48,280
Naruto felt an excruciating pain…

270
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:54,700
බැලූ බැල්මට 
පෙනෙන්නේ මෙම පුද්ගලයා ඔබට දරාගත හැකි ප්‍රමාණයට වඩා වැඩි බවයි.

271
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:59,200
ඊළඟ වතාවේ නරුටෝ ෂිප්පුඩන්: 
ජිරයියා කණ්ඩායම

272
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:02,280
දීර්ඝ කාලයක් දකින්න නැහැ!

273
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:04,990
JIRAIYA Ninja පාලුයි: 
ඔයාව වීරයා ද ටේල් ඔෆ් 
කණ්ඩායම JIRAIYA

274
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:16,990
නැවත සුසර කරන්න!

